
This diagram captures:

- Users and their relationship with accounts.
- The two types of accounts: `PersonalAccount` and `BusinessAccount`.
- The concept of `Page`, including the special type `AdvertisementPage`.
- Relationships between users, accounts, and pages.
- Constraints like one user per account and one admin per page.

---


@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

class User {
    - id : String (Unique)
    - name : String
    - email : String
    - dateOfBirth : Date
}

class Account {
    - accountNumber : String (Auto-generated)
    + createPage(name : String) : Page
    + grantPrivileges(user : User, page : Page) : void
}

abstract class AccountType {
    # monthlyFee : Boolean
    <<abstract>>
}

class PersonalAccount extends AccountType {
    # canSendFriendRequests() : Boolean
}

class BusinessAccount extends AccountType {
    - companyName : String
    # hasMonthlyFee : Boolean = true
}

class Page {
    - name : String
    - visits : Integer
    - admin : Account
    <<unique name per account>>
}

class AdvertisementPage extends Page {
    - bounceRate : Double
    - clickThroughRate : Double
    - conversionRate : Double
}

class FriendRequest {
    - sender : User
    - receiver : User
    - status : StatusEnum
}

enum StatusEnum {
    PENDING
    ACCEPTED
    REJECTED
}

' Relationships
User "1" -- "1" Account
Account "1" -- "0..*" Page
AccountType "1" ..|> Account
User "0..*" -- "0..*" FriendRequest
User "0..*" -- "0..*" FriendRequest : reverse

Page "1" -- "1" Account : administered by

' Note about constraints
note right of User
    A user can only have one account.
    No multiple accounts allowed.
end note

note right of Account
    An account is uniquely identified by an auto-generated account number.
    Each account can create multiple pages.
end note

note right of Page
    Each page must be administered by exactly one account.
    No two pages with the same name under the same account.
end note

@enduml

---

### 📌 Notes:
- `<<unique name per account>>` in the `Page` class indicates that within a single account, no two pages can share the same name.
- `AccountType` is abstract and serves as a base for both `PersonalAccount` and `BusinessAccount`.
- `FriendRequest` is a separate entity to model interactions between users (only for personal accounts).
- Constraints are noted directly in the diagram using `note` blocks.

